{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-aprender-10-teoria-dos-numeros-markdown-remark-frontmatter-slug-tsx","path":"/aprender/10-teoria-dos-numeros/forca-bruta-recursao-backtracking/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"01 - Força bruta, recursão e backtracking","description":"Tipos de algoritmos","author":"Arissa Yoshida, Nicolas Barbosa Gomes, Luis Henrique Morelli"},"html":"<h2 id=\"paradigmas-de-projeto-de-algoritmos\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#paradigmas-de-projeto-de-algoritmos\" aria-label=\"paradigmas de projeto de algoritmos permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Paradigmas de Projeto de Algoritmos</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Determinados problemas requerem abordagens adequadas em suas resoluções;</li>\n<li>Dependendo da estratégia adotada, o desempenho do algoritmo pode ser ineficiente, resultando em TLE;</li>\n<li>Os paradigmas são como estratégias de como abordar e modelar uma solução de maneira eficiente quando aplicados corretamente.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"exemplos\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#exemplos\" aria-label=\"exemplos permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Exemplos</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Indução Matemática</li>\n<li>Força Bruta</li>\n<li>Recursividade</li>\n<li>Backtracking (Tentativa e Erro)</li>\n<li>Algoritmos Gananciosos</li>\n<li>Divisão e Conquista</li>\n<li>Programação Dinâmica</li>\n<li>Algoritmos Aproximados (Heurísticas)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"força-bruta\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#for%C3%A7a-bruta\" aria-label=\"força bruta permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Força Bruta</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Algoritmos simples;</li>\n<li>Percorrem o espaço de busca do problema, procurando todas as possíveis soluções candidatas, verificando quais satisfazem a questão inicial;</li>\n<li>Varredura “cega”;</li>\n<li>Útil para pequenos problemas;</li>\n<li>Fácil implementação;</li>\n<li>Sempre que existir uma solução, o algoritmo irá encontrá-la.</li>\n<li>Exigem grande esforço computacional, seu custo tende a crescer exponencialmente.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"the-closest-pair-problem\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-closest-pair-problem\" aria-label=\"the closest pair problem permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The Closest Pair Problem</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Confira a GIF abaixo:</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"/static/gif1-b25239f1496c92e6242e02ed448bcda9.gif\" alt=\"img1-img4\"></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-cpp line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-cpp\"><span class=\"token keyword\">double</span> <span class=\"token function\">euclidean</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">double</span> x1<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">double</span> y1<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">double</span> x2<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">double</span> y2<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>x1 <span class=\"token operator\">-</span> x2<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>x1 <span class=\"token operator\">-</span> x2<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>y1 <span class=\"token operator\">-</span> y2<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>y1 <span class=\"token operator\">-</span> y2<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> <span class=\"token function\">main</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</spa